de.esoco.data.element

Class HierarchicalDataObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.esoco.data.element.HierarchicalDataObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    de.esoco.lib.model.DataModel<java.lang.String>, de.esoco.lib.model.HierarchicalDataModel<java.lang.String>, de.esoco.lib.property.Editable, de.esoco.lib.property.Flags<java.lang.String>, de.esoco.lib.property.HasId<java.lang.String>, de.esoco.lib.property.Indexed, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>

    public class HierarchicalDataObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements de.esoco.lib.model.HierarchicalDataModel<java.lang.String>, de.esoco.lib.property.HasId<java.lang.String>, de.esoco.lib.property.Flags<java.lang.String>, de.esoco.lib.property.Indexed, de.esoco.lib.property.Editable, java.io.Serializable
    A simple hierarchical data object to efficiently transfer query data between client and server. An object contains a list of string values and references to parent and child objects. It also implements HierarchicalDataModel so that it can be used directly in UI components.

    Serialized Form
